ring to a proper size for the door.";i:16;s:66:"A proper fitting spring makes for a balanced and safe garage door.";i:17;s:38:"Why Did The Garage Door Springs Break.";i:18;s:63:"Garage door springs break both by accident and through neglect.";i:19;s:61:"Below are a few examples of what can cause a spring to break.";i:20;s:41:"4 Reasons Garage Door Springs Break Rust.";i:21;s:46:"Springs made of metal are susceptible to rust.";i:22;s:134:"If your door is heavy and the springs are more than 4-years-old your springs are in the break range we recommend a spring replacement.";i:23;s:143:"If your garaged door is light then the springs may possibly be the wrong size and you should have it checked out by a professional garage door.";i:24;s:146:"In most cases you can determine the wind of your garage door torsion spring by using the color-coded system on the cones at the end of the spring.";i:25;s:73:"Usually you will have two springs on your door which will be color-coded.";i:26;s:56:"In MOST not all cases the end on the right hand wind is.";i:27;s:126:"With most new garage doors there will be two torsion springs separated by a divider thats located at the midpoint of the door.";i:28;s:102:"The spring to your right is a left wound spring and the spring to your left is the right wound spring.";i:29;s:60:"So if the spring to your left is broken you want to order a.";i:30;s:34:"This is what bad roller look like.";i:31;s:98:"If the coils are distended and irregular when the spring is extended then it needs to be replaced.";i:32;s:65:"You can see this when your garage door is in the closed position.";i:33;s:54:"Extension springs are attached to a pulley and I-bolt.";i:34;s:45:"The I-bolt is attached to a vertical bracket.";i:35;s:136:"Using the wrong size garage door springs will caused the to not function properly and could also cause the opener to break much quicker.";i:36;s:107:"Replacing extension springs can be very dangerous and if done wrong can harm someone using the garage door.";i:37;s:85:"Make sure you call the Garage Door Doctor to ensure your garage is repaired properly.";i:38;s:28:"Aladdin Doors to the rescue.";i:39;s:171:"When your garage door springs snap rollers fall off your door is off track or the opener is dead we offer same-day appointments and 247 support just when you need it most.";i:40;s:68:"Here are some of the top reasons your garage door system has failed.";i:41;s:76:"Broken torsion spring Did you just hear a loud bang coming from your garage.";i:42;s:58:"Did you notice that the spring along the top of your door.";i:43;s:38:"Worn-out or broken garage door spring.";i:44;s:51:"This is the main reason why your garage door slams.";i:45;s:18:"Why do I say this.";i:46;s:89:"The garage door spring is responsible for carrying the entire weight of your garage door.";i:47;s:109:"The tension in the springs keeps the door open when it is fully opened and holds it when it is being dropped.";}}